      en_IN: "**Menstruation - Period Advice & Management**\n\n**Normal Period Information**:\n‚Ä¢ Average cycle: 21-35 days\n‚Ä¢ Flow lasts: 3-7 days\n‚Ä¢ Normal flow: 30-40ml per day\n‚Ä¢ First periods may be irregular (normal!)\n\n**Managing Period Cramps**:\n1. **Heat therapy** (most effective!):\n   ‚Ä¢ Hot water bottle on lower abdomen\n   ‚Ä¢ Heating pad for 15-20 minutes\n   ‚Ä¢ Warm shower or bath\n2. **Exercise**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Light walking\n   ‚Ä¢ Gentle yoga\n   ‚Ä¢ Stretching\n   ‚Ä¢ Helps release endorphins\n3. **Medication**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Ibuprofen (400mg) - Most effective\n   ‚Ä¢ Paracetamol (500mg)\n   ‚Ä¢ Take at first sign of cramps\n4. **Dietary support**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Increase calcium: milk, yogurt, cheese\n   ‚Ä¢ Magnesium: dark chocolate, nuts, seeds\n   ‚Ä¢ Iron: meat, beans, spinach\n   ‚Ä¢ Stay hydrated: drink 8-10 glasses water\n5. **Rest**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Get enough sleep\n   ‚Ä¢ Reduce stress\n   ‚Ä¢ Light activity preferred over bed rest\n\n**Heavy Periods - When to Seek Help**:\nüö® Call doctor if:\n‚Ä¢ Soaking through 1+ pads/tampons per hour for several hours\n‚Ä¢ Bleeding lasting >7 days\n‚Ä¢ Large clots (bigger than a coin)\n‚Ä¢ Severe anemia symptoms (weakness, dizziness, shortness of breath)\n‚Ä¢ Interfering with daily life\n\n**Irregular Periods**:\n‚Ä¢ First 1-3 years: Often irregular (NORMAL)\n‚Ä¢ Causes: Stress, diet changes, exercise, weight changes\n‚Ä¢ Usually settles down after age 20\n‚Ä¢ Track periods: helps doctor diagnose issues\n\n**Hygiene Tips**:\n1. **Use proper products**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Pads: change every 4-6 hours\n   ‚Ä¢ Tampons: change every 4-8 hours\n   ‚Ä¢ Menstrual cups: empty every 12 hours\n2. **Maintain hygiene**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Wash hands before & after changing\n   ‚Ä¢ Wash vulva gently with water\n   ‚Ä¢ Change clothes/bed sheets regularly\n   ‚Ä¢ Never flush pads/tampons (environmental risk)\n3. **Prevention**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Don't douche (kills good bacteria)\n   ‚Ä¢ Avoid strong soaps (use water)\n   ‚Ä¢ Wear breathable underwear\n\n**Foods that help**:\n‚úÖ Dark leafy greens (iron)\n‚úÖ Nuts & seeds (magnesium)\n‚úÖ Fatty fish (omega-3)\n‚úÖ Dark chocolate (mood + magnesium)\n‚úÖ Ginger tea (reduces inflammation)\n‚ùå Avoid: Excessive caffeine, salt, sugar\n\n**Emotional Support**:\n‚Ä¢ PMS/period mood changes are NORMAL\n‚Ä¢ Hormones affect neurotransmitters\n‚Ä¢ Exercise & sunlight help mood\n‚Ä¢ Talk to someone if feelings are severe\n\n**What's NOT normal - See doctor**:\n‚Ä¢ Missed period for 2+ months\n‚Ä¢ Severe pain (can't function)\n‚Ä¢ Excessive bleeding\n‚Ä¢ Foul-smelling discharge\n‚Ä¢ Fever with heavy bleeding\n\n**Tracking your cycle**:\n‚Ä¢ Use calendar app or notebook\n‚Ä¢ Track: start date, end date, symptoms\n‚Ä¢ Helps identify patterns\n‚Ä¢ Useful for doctor visits\n\n‚úÖ **Remember: Periods are normal and healthy!** Manage discomfort and live your life normally.",
