      en_IN: "Controlling a Nosebleed:\n\n1. **Immediate action**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Sit upright (don't lie back)\n   ‚Ä¢ Lean forward slightly\n   ‚Ä¢ Don't tilt head back\n2. **Apply pressure**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Pinch nose firmly (just below bridge)\n   ‚Ä¢ Hold for 10-15 minutes continuously\n   ‚Ä¢ Don't release to check\n   ‚Ä¢ Use clean cloth or tissue\n3. **Keep cool**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Apply ice pack to bridge of nose\n   ‚Ä¢ Or cold compress to cheeks\n   ‚Ä¢ This constricts blood vessels\n4. **Breathe through mouth** - Don't sniff\n5. **After 10-15 minutes**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Gently release pressure\n   ‚Ä¢ If still bleeding, repeat for another 10 minutes\n6. **Once stopped**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Don't blow nose forcefully for 24 hours\n   ‚Ä¢ Avoid hot drinks\n   ‚Ä¢ Keep head elevated\n   ‚Ä¢ Don't pick or scratch nose\n\n**Prevention**:\n‚Ä¢ Use saline nasal drops\n‚Ä¢ Humidify air in dry months\n‚Ä¢ Avoid picking nose\n‚Ä¢ Avoid forceful sneezing\n‚Ä¢ Keep nasal passages moist\n\n**When to see doctor**:\n‚Ä¢ Bleeding lasts more than 30 minutes\n‚Ä¢ Frequent nosebleeds\n‚Ä¢ Bleeding after head injury\n‚Ä¢ Accompanied by other symptoms\n‚Ä¢ Heavy bleeding\n\nMost nosebleeds stop on their own!",
