      en_IN: "First Aid for Sprains & Strains:\n\n**Immediate Treatment - RICE**:\n1. **R - Rest** (First 24-48 hours):\n   ‚Ä¢ Stop activity immediately\n   ‚Ä¢ Avoid weight-bearing if leg involved\n   ‚Ä¢ Use crutches if needed\n2. **I - Ice**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Apply ice pack for 15-20 minutes\n   ‚Ä¢ Every 2-3 hours for first 48 hours\n   ‚Ä¢ Reduces swelling and pain\n3. **C - Compression**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Wrap with elastic bandage\n   ‚Ä¢ Firm but not cutting off circulation\n   ‚Ä¢ Keep on for 48-72 hours\n4. **E - Elevation**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Keep injured area above heart\n   ‚Ä¢ Helps reduce swelling\n   ‚Ä¢ Sleep with pillow supporting limb\n\n**Pain Management**:\n‚Ä¢ Paracetamol or Ibuprofen\n‚Ä¢ Apply pain relief gel\n\n**After 48-72 hours**:\n‚Ä¢ Start gentle movement\n‚Ä¢ Gradual increase in activity\n‚Ä¢ Apply heat instead of ice\n‚Ä¢ Massage around (not on) injury\n\n**Physical Therapy**:\n‚Ä¢ Specific exercises for that joint\n‚Ä¢ Improves strength and flexibility\n‚Ä¢ Prevents re-injury\n\n**When to see doctor**:\n‚Ä¢ Severe swelling that increases\n‚Ä¢ Unable to move joint\n‚Ä¢ Severe pain that won't subside\n‚Ä¢ Possible fracture (can't bear weight)\n‚Ä¢ Swelling doesn't improve after 3 days\n\n**Recovery time**:\n‚Ä¢ Mild: 2-3 weeks\n‚Ä¢ Moderate: 4-6 weeks\n‚Ä¢ Severe: 8-12 weeks",
