      en_IN: "Managing Insect Bites & Stings:\n\n**Immediate First Aid**:\n1. **Remove stinger** (if bee sting):\n   ‚Ä¢ Scrape with flat edge (card, knife)\n   ‚Ä¢ Don't squeeze (releases venom)\n   ‚Ä¢ Remove quickly\n2. **Clean the area**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Wash with soap and water\n   ‚Ä¢ Use antiseptic\n3. **Apply ice**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Ice pack for 10-15 minutes\n   ‚Ä¢ Reduces swelling and itching\n4. **Reduce itching**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Apply hydrocortisone cream\n   ‚Ä¢ Antihistamine tablet\n   ‚Ä¢ Calamine lotion\n   ‚Ä¢ Cold compress\n5. **Don't scratch**:\n   ‚Ä¢ Scratching causes infection\n   ‚Ä¢ Keep nails trimmed\n   ‚Ä¢ Wear gloves if sleeping\n\n**Pain & Swelling**:\n‚Ä¢ Paracetamol or Ibuprofen\n‚Ä¢ Elevation if on limb\n‚Ä¢ Apply heat after 24 hours\n\n**Prevention**:\n‚Ä¢ Use insect repellent\n‚Ä¢ Wear long sleeves in evening\n‚Ä¢ Avoid bright colors outdoors\n‚Ä¢ Keep mosquito nets clean\n‚Ä¢ Avoid stagnant water\n\n**When to seek help**:\n‚Ä¢ Severe swelling (larger than 10cm)\n‚Ä¢ Multiple stings\n‚Ä¢ Sting in mouth or throat\n‚Ä¢ Signs of infection\n‚Ä¢ Allergic reaction (difficulty breathing, severe swelling)\n‚Ä¢ CALL 112 for allergic reaction\n\n**Recovery**:\nMost bites heal in 1-2 weeks",
